## What an AI Engineer Actually Does

Most AI engineers don't train models from scratch. They **build products and systems on top of existing models**. That typically includes:

- Connecting to LLM APIs
- Designing prompts and context flows
- Building chat, search, or automation systems
- Integrating tools, databases, and external APIs
- Handling structured outputs
- Improving reliability, cost, and latency
- Deploying AI features into real applications

In practice, an AI engineer sits somewhere between software engineering, product engineering, automation, and applied AI.

If you can build real LLM apps, retrieval systems, automations, and production-ready workflows, you're already much closer to being employable than most beginners.

